 in climate change. A key notion here is that of a public Sabbath, or a 'workplace of hope'-times and places set aside to cultivate inspiration and mutual trust among all parties involved, enabling them to take concrete steps forward.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aClimatic changesxEconomic aspects. 0aClimatic changesxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aEcotheology. 0aHope. 4aContemporary Society. 4aEconomics and Finance. 4aEnvironment and Sustainability. 4aInterdisciplinary Studies. 4aReligion and Philosophy. 4aReligion and Theology. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Theory.2bisacsh  atheology, economics, climate change, Jonathan Sacks, radical uncertainty, hope.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishz978311131907008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2023z9783111318134oZDB-23-DBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048558483?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048558483zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048558483/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131907-0 EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB